node.text:
You got to a pool party & these are on the charcuterie board - What do you do?

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon olive oil
1 onion, finely chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 1/2 pounds russet potatoes, peeled and quartered
1 cup whole milk, divided
5 tablespoons butter, cubed
Sea salt
1 cup fresh breadcrumbs
1/2 cup fresh herbs (thyme, rosemary, parsley), chopped
Zest of 1 lemon
1/4 cup tomato paste
1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
1 large egg
1/2 cup grated carrots
1 1/3 lbs ground beef
48 slices prosciutto
Freshly grated Parmesan cheese
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven 350°F, and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

2. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.

3. Add in onion and sauté, stirring occasionally until golden, about 8 minutes.

4. Add in garlic and cook, stirring often, 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and let mixture cool slightly.

5. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat.

6. Add in potatoes and cook, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until completely tender. Drain well.

7. Transfer potatoes back to pot and mash until smooth.

8. Add in 3/4 cup milk and butter, and fold in with a spatula until well combined. Liberally season with salt to taste.

9. In a large bowl, mix together breadcrumbs and remaining 1/4 cup milk, and let sit 5 minutes to soften.

10. Add in onion and garlic mixture, along with herbs, lemon zest, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, egg, carrots and ground beef. Season with a large pinch of salt.

11. Place 2 slices of prosciutto in each cup of 2 standard size muffin tins, making sure to fully cover the bottom and the sides, leaving about 1/2 inch overhang on all sides.

12. Firmly press about 1/4 to 1/3 cup ground beef mixture into each prosciutto-lined mold.

13. Bake in oven 20 mins.

14. Remove meatloaves from tins and place on the prepared baking sheet.

15. Top each meatloaf with 3 tbsp mashed potatoes.

16. Grate Parmesan cheese over each meatloaf.

17. Preheat broiler to high and broil for 8 to 10 mins until tops are golden.

18. Serve immediately with roasted tomato jam or ketchup, if desired.

node.title: Finally, meatloaf you can eat on the go!

Ingredients:

3 small red potatoes, halved
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
1/4 cup sliced fresh chives
1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese, plus more for sprinkling
1/2 cup cold unsalted butter
1 tablespoon butter, melted
3/4 cup buttermilk
1/4 cup unsalted butter
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon onion salt
2 cups beef broth

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.

2. Thinly slice each potato lengthwise without cutting all the way through, leaving them hinged together. Set aside.

3. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cheese and chives.

4. Add 1/2 cup butter and pulse to a coarse consistency. Add buttermilk while pulsing until the dough comes together.

5. Transfer to the cast-iron skillet, and make 6 wells around the center.

6. Gently press potato halves, flat-side down, into the wells in the biscuit dough. Brush the potatoes and biscuit top with the melted butter.

7. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the biscuit dough is golden. Cool slightly, then slice.

8. In a saucepan, heat the butter on medium. Add flour and cook until bubbling, about 2 minutes.

9. Add onion salt and beef broth and cook until thickened. Pour over slices of potato biscuits and serve.

node.title: Who needs a "main course" when this potato biscuit pie exists? 🥧

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Ingredients:

300g cooked macaroni
30g plain flour
30g butter
400ml whole milk
200g cheddar, grated
100g mozzarella, grated
50g parmesan, grated
1 cup yellow cornmeal
90g all-purpose flour
1 heaped tbsp caster sugar
2 tsp baking powder
Salt and freshly ground pepper
1 large egg, lightly beaten
110ml whole milk
2l veg oil for frying

Steps:

1. Melt the butter in a pan and then add the flour and stir straight away. Let this colour slightly and then start pouring in the milk a little at a time, whisking after each pour.

2. Once all added stir through all the cheeses followed by the pasta. Once all well mixed, leave to cool.

3. Divide the mixture into 8 and place onto 8 large pieces of cling film. Shape into sausages, and roll the cling film tightly around it, twisting the ends so nothing escapes. Place in the fridge to harden and cool, and then skewer. Place back in the fridge whilst you start making the batter.

4. Whisk together all the dry ingredients. Whisk the eggs and then add this to the dry ingredients along with the milk. Set aside to thicken slightly, and heat the oil to 180C.

5. Dip the mac and cheese into the batter making sure it’s completely covered. Repeat with the rest placing on a tray as you go.

6. Cook in the hot oil for a few minutes until golden all over. Repeat with the remaining mac and cheese dogs. Blot before serving.

node.title: This mac 'n' cheese is pretending to be a corn dog, and we're not mad.

Ingredients:

1 cup chopped fresh chives
1 bunch scallions, ends trimmed, roughly chopped
1/2 cup olive oil
1/4 cup white cheddar cheese
1/4 cup Parmesan cheese
3/4 cup warm milk
1 packet active dry yeast
1 1/2 cups bread flour
2 teaspoons sea salt
1 cup sour cream
2 teaspoons onion salt

Steps:

1. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, pulse chives and scallions to a mince.

2. Add olive oil and pulse to combine. Stir in cheeses, and set aside.

3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and prepare a baking sheet with parchment paper.

4. In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk. Add the flour and sea salt, and knead well. Cover and let rest for 1 hour.

5. In a small bowl, mix sour cream and onion salt, and divide the mixture in half.

6. On a floured surface, roll out the dough to a 6 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread half the sour cream over the dough. Drizzle the pesto over the sour cream.

7. Roll the dough lengthwise into a large tube. With a sharp knife, cut in half lengthwise to reveal the center. Transfer to the prepared baking sheet, and braid with the open center facing up.

8. Bake for 35 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with remaining sour cream and onion dip.

🎥: @tastemadebr 

Ingredients:

3 avocados
1/2 red onion, chopped
2 tomatoes, chopped
1 Brazilian aji pepper, chopped
1/4 bunch cilantro, chopped
1/2 lime
1, 10 1/2-ounce bag Doritos
1 chicken breast, cut into strips
Salt
1 cup wheat flour
1 tablespoon spicy paprika
1 tablespoon onion powder
2 eggs, lightly beaten
Frying oil

Steps:

1. Cut the avocados, remove the pit (do not discard), remove the peel and chop into cubes.

2. Arrange the chopped avocados in a bowl and add the onion, tomatoes, pepper, cilantro and juice of half a lime. Mix thoroughly, salt to taste, and set aside in the refrigerator. (Tip: Store the guacamole with the core inside to stop avocado from becoming dark.)

3. Into a blender or food processor, add the Doritos. Crush into smaller pieces.

4. Season the chicken with salt.

5. In a bowl, combine the flour, paprika and onion powder.

6. Dip the chicken pieces in wheat flour, then in the beaten eggs, and finally the crushed Doritos.

7. Fry in hot oil until golden and crispy. Drain on paper towels.

8. Serve with guacamole.

node.title: Elevate your chicken tender game with these Doritos-crusted strips.

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Ingredients:

20g unsalted butter
1 tin condensed milk
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
100g plain flour
40g cocoa powder
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
120g softened butter
40g light brown sugar
100g caster sugar
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1 egg
Vanilla ice cream, to serve

Steps:

1. To make the Brazilian fudge, melt all the ingredients together in a saucepan over a medium heat for 15 minutes, or until the mixture has thickened. Keep stirring so it doesn’t stick to the bottom of the pan!

2. When thickened, pour the mixture onto a greased plate to cool.

3. Preheat the oven to 180C/160C fan.

4. In a bowl cream together the butter and sugars until light and fluffy then mix in the egg and vanilla and stir to combine. Fold in the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt.

5. Grease a 20cm cast iron pan and place ½ of the cookie mix in the bottom.

6. Roll the fudge into a circle roughly 16cm in diameter - so that it will sit on top of the cookie mixture and not touch the sides of the pan and place on top of the cookie mixture. Spread the rest of the cookie mixture on top and place in the oven for 25 - 30 minutes or until set on top but still soft in the middle. Take out of the oven and leave in the pan to cool for 5 minutes.

7. Serve with big scoops of vanilla ice cream on top and eat straight from the pan.

node.title: The deeper the dish, the better the cookie.

Ingredients:

1 pie crust, store-bought or homemade
1/4 cup unsalted butter, room temperature
1/2 cup brown sugar
2 teaspoons cinnamon
3/4 cup light corn syrup
1/4 cup dark corn syrup
1 cup of brown sugar
3/4 teaspoon salt
1 1/2 cups pecan pieces, toasted
3 eggs
2 teaspoons vanilla extract
1 cup pecan halves
1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened
1 cup powdered sugar
1 tablespoon bourbon (or bourbon extract)
1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

2. In a small bowl, mix together butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.

3. On a floured work surface, roll out pie crust and slather on cinnamon roll filling.

4. Starting with the side closest to you, roll into a tight log. Trim about 1 or 2 inches off each end and discard.

5. Cut each log into 1/2-inch thick pieces (you should get about 18 to 20).

6. On a floured surface, roll out each piece to 1/4-inch thick and press into a 9-inch pie pan. Chill until firm while preparing filling.

7. In a bowl, whisk together light and dark corn syrup, brown sugar, salt, toasted pecan pieces (not halves), eggs, and vanilla extract. Mix until incorporated.

8. Pour into prepared crust and top with pecan halves, arranging in a circle.

9. Bake for about 1 hour or until firm.

10. Let cool fully before slicing. Serve with Bourbon Vanilla Icing.

11. Whisk together ingredients until smooth.

12. Set aside and decorate pie when cool.

node.title: Keep your eyes on on the (cinnamon roll pecan) pie. 🥧

Sweet Potato Curley Fries With Avocado Ranch

Ingredients:

4 medium sweet potatoes
2 tablespoons potato starch
Cooking spray
1 ripe avocado
1/2 teaspoon white wine vinegar
4 tablespoons low-fat creme fraiche
1/8 teaspoon salt
1/8 teaspoon dried parsley
1/8 teaspoon dried dill
1/8 teaspoon onion powder
1/8 teaspoon hot paprika
A few chives, finely chopped

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees, and lightly oil a large baking tray.

2. Carefully skewer each potato, lengthways, as close to the middle as you can.

3. With a paring knife, make one long incision from the top of the potato to the bottom while spiraling around the skewer. Repeat with the rest.

4. Dust each spiral with potato starch, making sure it gets in between the layers, then place on the tray.

5. Spray each potato with oil, then bake for 30 minutes, turning a few times to ensure even cooking.

6. Once the fries are cooked and crisp, remove them from the oven and carefully slide them off the skewer.

7. Serve immediately alongside avocado ranch dressing.

8. In the bowl of a food processor, add the avocado flesh and vinegar, and blitz until smooth.

9. Add in the creme fraiche, salt, parsley, dill, onion powder and hot paprika and blitz again until creamy.

10. Put the dressing into a small bowl and stir in the chopped chives.

11. Sprinkle a few chives and a pinch of paprika on top.

node.title: Sweet potatoes fries are best when eaten with avocado ranch.

You got to a pool party & these are on the charcuterie board - What do you do?

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon olive oil
1 onion, finely chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 1/2 pounds russet potatoes, peeled and quartered
1 cup whole milk, divided
5 tablespoons butter, cubed
Sea salt
1 cup fresh breadcrumbs
1/2 cup fresh herbs (thyme, rosemary, parsley), chopped
Zest of 1 lemon
1/4 cup tomato paste
1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
1 large egg
1/2 cup grated carrots
1 1/3 lbs ground beef
48 slices prosciutto
Freshly grated Parmesan cheese
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven 350°F, and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

2. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.

3. Add in onion and sauté, stirring occasionally until golden, about 8 minutes.

4. Add in garlic and cook, stirring often, 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and let mixture cool slightly.

5. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat.

6. Add in potatoes and cook, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until completely tender. Drain well.

7. Transfer potatoes back to pot and mash until smooth.

8. Add in 3/4 cup milk and butter, and fold in with a spatula until well combined. Liberally season with salt to taste.

9. In a large bowl, mix together breadcrumbs and remaining 1/4 cup milk, and let sit 5 minutes to soften.

10. Add in onion and garlic mixture, along with herbs, lemon zest, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, egg, carrots and ground beef. Season with a large pinch of salt.

11. Place 2 slices of prosciutto in each cup of 2 standard size muffin tins, making sure to fully cover the bottom and the sides, leaving about 1/2 inch overhang on all sides.

12. Firmly press about 1/4 to 1/3 cup ground beef mixture into each prosciutto-lined mold.

13. Bake in oven 20 mins.

14. Remove meatloaves from tins and place on the prepared baking sheet.

15. Top each meatloaf with 3 tbsp mashed potatoes.

16. Grate Parmesan cheese over each meatloaf.

17. Preheat broiler to high and broil for 8 to 10 mins until tops are golden.

18. Serve immediately with roasted tomato jam or ketchup, if desired.

node.text:
Forget the chips and dip, French dip sliders are the best way to feed a crowd. 

Ingredients:

Butter, for greasing pan
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 large onion, sliced
3 cloves garlic, minced
Kosher salt, to taste
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste
1/3 cup mayonnaise
1 tablespoon prepared horseradish
2 teaspoons Dijon mustard
1 (24-ounce) bag King's Hawaiian Original sweet rolls
1 1/4 pounds roast beef, thinly sliced
10 slices Swiss cheese
1/4 cup butter, melted
2 tablespoons butter
1 tablespoon flour
1 (14-ounce) can beef stock
Dash of cooking sherry (optional)

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter a 9x13 baking dish.

2. Heat olive oil in a large sauté pan over medium heat. Add onions and sauté until tender and caramelized, about 10 minutes.

3. Add garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 more minute. Season with salt and pepper.

4. In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, horseradish and Dijon. Set aside.

5. Slice the entire package of rolls in half without separating them into rolls.

6. Place the bottom layer of rolls into the prepared baking dish. Spread with the mayonnaise mixture, then top with the caramelized onions, roast beef and Swiss cheese. Top with the other half of the rolls and brush with melted butter.

7. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is melted and rolls are golden brown.

8. For the au jus, melt 2 tablespoons butter in a medium saucepan. Sprinkle in flour and stir with a wooden spoon until pasty.

9. Whisk in beef stock, bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer and season with a dash of cooking sherry (optional). Serve alongside the sliders.

#ad Looking for a shortcut to get more greens and protein in your day? We've got just the thing: bake up this super greens frittata made with @lactaid Protein 2% Reduced Fat Milk — 100% Real Milk, just without the lactose! 

Protein Packed Super Greens Frittata

Ingredients:

8 large eggs
½ cup Lactaid® Protein 2% Reduced Fat Milk
½ bunch parsley, chopped
½ bunch dill, chopped
3 cups greens of your choice, chopped (chard, kale, spinach)
1 Serrano, seeded and chopped
2 tablespoons olive oil
4 cloves garlic, chopped
Salt and pepper to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

2. In a medium mixing bowl combine the eggs and milk. Thoroughly whisk and season with salt and pepper.

3. Heat a cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. Add two tablespoons of olive oil and saute Serrano and garlic until fragrant. Add in the greens and saute until wilted.

4. Add in the fresh herbs, slightly saute and then add in the egg mixture. Place the cast iron skillet into the preheated oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until the frittata has set.

5. Slice, top with more fresh herbs, and enjoy!

Ingredients:

3 small red potatoes, halved
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
1/4 cup sliced fresh chives
1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese, plus more for sprinkling
1/2 cup cold unsalted butter
1 tablespoon butter, melted
3/4 cup buttermilk
1/4 cup unsalted butter
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon onion salt
2 cups beef broth

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.

2. Thinly slice each potato lengthwise without cutting all the way through, leaving them hinged together. Set aside.

3. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cheese and chives.

4. Add 1/2 cup butter and pulse to a coarse consistency. Add buttermilk while pulsing until the dough comes together.

5. Transfer to the cast-iron skillet, and make 6 wells around the center.

6. Gently press potato halves, flat-side down, into the wells in the biscuit dough. Brush the potatoes and biscuit top with the melted butter.

7. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the biscuit dough is golden. Cool slightly, then slice.

8. In a saucepan, heat the butter on medium. Add flour and cook until bubbling, about 2 minutes.

9. Add onion salt and beef broth and cook until thickened. Pour over slices of potato biscuits and serve.
